     1→# Tailwind CSS + Astro + Vue 3 Best Practices (2024-2025)
     2→
     3→**Research Date:** 2025-10-22
     4→**Focus:** Configuration architecture, animations, SSR patterns, plugin design
     5→
     6→---
     7→
     8→## Executive Summary
     9→
    10→Tailwind CSS v4 introduced major architectural changes that fundamentally alter configuration patterns. The shift from `tailwind.config.js` to CSS-first configuration via `@theme` directive provides cleaner theme management, better type safety, and simplified multi-theme implementations. Astro + Vue 3 integration benefits from these patterns through improved SSR safety and hydration management.
    11→
    12→**Key Findings:**
    13→- Tailwind v4 uses `@theme` directive in CSS files instead of JavaScript config
    14→- `darkMode: "selector"` (v3) becomes `darkMode: "class"` for Astro SSR compatibility
    15→- Animation systems should centralize tokens via `@theme` with JavaScript/Vue integration via CSS variables
    16→- Custom utilities via `@utility` directive preferred over full plugins for most cases
    17→- Astro View Transitions require special dark mode persistence patterns
    18→
    19→---
    20→
    21→## 1. Tailwind Config Architecture
    22→
    23→### v4 Paradigm Shift: CSS-First Configuration
    24→
    25→**Source:** https://tailwindcss.com/docs/theme
    26→
    27→Tailwind v4 eliminates `tailwind.config.js` in favor of CSS-based configuration using the `@theme` directive.
    28→
    29→#### `@theme` Directive Fundamentals
    30→
    31→**Core difference from `:root`:**
    32→- `@theme` variables generate utility classes AND create CSS variables
    33→- `:root` variables are purely stylistic (no utilities generated)
    34→- Use `@theme` for design tokens, `:root` for internal CSS-only values
    35→
    36→**Theme Variable Namespaces:**
    37→
    38→| Namespace | Generated Utilities | Example |
    39→|-----------|-------------------|---------|
    40→| `--color-*` | `bg-`, `text-`, `border-`, `fill-` | `--color-primary: #3f3cbb` |
    41→| `--font-*` | `font-sans`, `font-serif` | `--font-display: Poppins, sans-serif` |
    42→| `--spacing-*` | `px-`, `py-`, `gap-`, `max-h-` | `--spacing-7: 1.75rem` |
    43→| `--radius-*` | `rounded-sm`, `rounded-lg` | `--radius-xl: 1rem` |
    44→| `--shadow-*` | `shadow-md`, `shadow-lg` | `--shadow-brutal: 4px 4px 0 #000` |
    45→| `--breakpoint-*` | `sm:*`, `md:*`, `lg:*` | `--breakpoint-tablet: 48rem` |
    46→
    47→#### Configuration Patterns
    48→
    49→**1. Extending Default Theme (Recommended for Most Cases):**
    50→
    51→```css
    52→@import "tailwindcss";
    53→
    54→@theme {
    55→  /* Adds to existing colors, doesn't replace */
    56→  --color-brand-primary: #3f3cbb;
    57→  --color-brand-secondary: #f59e0b;
    58→
    59→  /* Custom font families */
    60→  --font-display: Poppins, sans-serif;
    61→  --font-body: Inter, system-ui, sans-serif;
    62→
    63→  /* Custom spacing tokens */
    64→  --spacing-18: 4.5rem;
    65→  --spacing-128: 32rem;
    66→}
    67→```
    68→
    69→**2. Overriding Default Values:**
    70→
    71→```css
    72→@theme {
    73→  /* Changes existing breakpoint */
    74→  --breakpoint-sm: 30rem; /* was 40rem */
    75→
    76→  /* Replaces default shadow */
    77→  --shadow-xl: 0 20px 25px -5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
    78→}
    79→```
    80→
    81→**3. Complete Namespace Replacement:**
    82→
    83→```css
    84→@theme {
    85→  /* Remove ALL default colors */
    86→  --color-*: initial;
    87→
    88→  /* Define only your custom palette */
    89→  --color-primary: #3f3cbb;
    90→  --color-secondary: #f59e0b;
    91→  --color-neutral-50: #fafafa;
    92→  --color-neutral-900: #171717;
    93→}
    94→```
    95→
    96→**⚠️ Warning:** Complete replacement removes utility classes like `bg-red-500`, `text-blue-600`, etc.
    97→
    98→#### Advanced Techniques
    99→
   100→**Referencing Other Variables:**
   101→
   102→```css
   103→@theme inline {
   104→  /* inline option prevents CSS variable resolution issues */
   105→  --font-sans: var(--font-inter);
   106→  --color-accent: var(--color-brand-primary);
   107→}
   108→```
   109→
   110→**Animation Keyframes in @theme:**
   111→
   112→```css
   113→@theme {
   114→  --animate-fade-in: fade-in 0.3s ease-out;
   115→  --animate-slide-up: slide-up 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
   116→
   117→  @keyframes fade-in {
   118→    from { opacity: 0; }
   119→    to { opacity: 1; }
   120→  }
   121→
   122→  @keyframes slide-up {
   123→    from { transform: translateY(1rem); opacity: 0; }
   124→    to { transform: translateY(0); opacity: 1; }
   125→  }
   126→}
   127→```
   128→
   129→**Sharing Across Projects (Monorepo Pattern):**
   130→
   131→```css
   132→/* packages/design-tokens/theme.css */
   133→@theme {
   134→  --color-brand-primary: #3f3cbb;
   135→  --color-brand-secondary: #f59e0b;
   136→  /* ... all shared tokens */
   137→}
   138→
   139→/* apps/marketing/styles/global.css */
   140→@import "@company/design-tokens/theme.css";
   141→@import "tailwindcss";
   142→```
   143→
   144→---
   145→
   146→## 2. Custom Color Palette Organization
   147→
   148→### Semantic Naming with Dark Mode Support
   149→
   150→**Source:** https://simonswiss.com/posts/tailwind-v4-multi-theme
   151→
   152→Tailwind v4 drastically simplifies multi-theme implementation by eliminating the need for RGB channel workarounds required in v3.
   153→
   154→#### v3 vs v4 Comparison
   155→
   156→**v3 Pattern (Complex, Error-Prone):**
   157→```javascript
   158→// tailwind.config.js
   159→module.exports = {
   160→  theme: {
   161→    colors: {
   162→      primary: 'rgb(var(--color-primary) / <alpha-value>)',
   163→    }
   164→  }
   165→}
   166→```
   167→```css
   168→:root {
   169→  --color-primary: 59 130 246; /* RGB channels only */
   170→}
   171→```
   172→
   173→**v4 Pattern (Simple, Intuitive):**
   174→```css
   175→@theme {
   176→  --color-primary: #3b82f6; /* Any valid color format */
   177→}
   178→```
   179→
   180→#### Multi-Theme Architecture
   181→
   182→**Base Theme Definition:**
   183→```css
   184→@import "tailwindcss";
   185→
   186→@theme {
   187→  /* Default/light theme colors */
   188→  --color-background: #ffffff;
   189→  --color-foreground: #171717;
   190→  --color-primary: #3f3cbb;
   191→  --color-secondary: #f59e0b;
   192→  --color-accent: #ec4899;
   193→  --color-muted: #f5f5f5;
   194→  --color-border: #e5e5e5;
   195→}
   196→```
   197→
   198→**Theme Variants:**
   199→```css
   200→@layer base {
   201→  /* Dark mode */
   202→  .dark {
   203→    --color-background: #0a0a0a;
   204→    --color-foreground: #fafafa;
   205→    --color-primary: #818cf8;
   206→    --color-secondary: #fbbf24;
   207→    --color-accent: #f9a8d4;
   208→    --color-muted: #262626;
   209→    --color-border: #404040;
   210→  }
   211→
   212→  /* Custom themes via data attributes */
   213→  [data-theme='ocean'] {
   214→    --color-primary: #aab9ff;
   215→    --color-secondary: #56d0a0;
   216→  }
   217→
   218→  [data-theme='rainforest'] {
   219→    --color-primary: #56d0a0;
   220→    --color-secondary: #34d399;
   221→  }
   222→
   223→  [data-theme='candy'] {
   224→    --color-primary: #f9a8d4;
   225→    --color-secondary: #fb7185;
   226→  }
   227→}
   228→```
   229→
   230→**Usage in Markup:**
   231→```html
   232→<!-- Automatic utility class generation -->
   233→<div class="bg-primary text-foreground">
   234→  <button class="bg-accent hover:bg-accent/90">Click me</button>
   235→</div>
   236→
   237→<!-- Arbitrary value syntax for theme variables -->
   238→<div class="bg-(--color-primary)"></div>
   239→```
   240→
   241→#### Semantic Color Strategy (Recommended)
   242→
   243→**Role-Based Naming:**
   244→```css
   245→@theme {
   246→  /* Surface colors */
   247→  --color-background: #ffffff;
   248→  --color-surface: #f9fafb;
   249→  --color-surface-elevated: #ffffff;
   250→
   251→  /* Text colors */
   252→  --color-foreground: #171717;
   253→  --color-muted-foreground: #737373;
   254→
   255→  /* Interactive states */
   256→  --color-primary: #3f3cbb;
   257→  --color-primary-hover: #312e81;
   258→  --color-destructive: #dc2626;
   259→  --color-destructive-hover: #b91c1c;
   260→
   261→  /* Borders and dividers */
   262→  --color-border: #e5e5e5;
   263→  --color-input-border: #d4d4d4;
   264→  --color-ring: #3f3cbb; /* Focus rings */
   265→}
   266→```
   267→
   268→**Benefits:**
   269→- Component-agnostic (works across design systems)
   270→- Easy theme switching (override semantic tokens)
   271→- Predictable dark mode (same utility classes, different values)
   272→
   273→---
   274→
   275→## 3. Animation & Motion Systems
   276→
   277→### Centralized Animation Tokens
   278→
   279→**Sources:**
   280→- https://motion.dev/docs/react-tailwind
   281→- https://tailwindcss.com/docs/animation
   282→
   283→#### Architecture Strategy: Tailwind for Static, Motion for Dynamic
   284→
   285→**Key Principle:** Let each library do what it does best:
   286→- **Tailwind:** Static animations (transitions, keyframes)
   287→- **Motion/Vue Animations:** Dynamic, interactive animations (gestures, layout shifts)
   288→
   289→#### Tailwind Animation Configuration
   290→
   291→**Define Animation Tokens:**
   292→```css
   293→@theme {
   294→  /* Animation durations */
   295→  --animate-duration-fast: 150ms;
   296→  --animate-duration-base: 300ms;
   297→  --animate-duration-slow: 500ms;
   298→
   299→  /* Easing functions */
   300→  --ease-in-out: cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
   301→  --ease-spring: cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1);
   302→
   303→  /* Predefined animations */
   304→  --animate-fade-in: fade-in var(--animate-duration-base) var(--ease-in-out);
   305→  --animate-slide-up: slide-up var(--animate-duration-base) var(--ease-in-out);
   306→  --animate-scale-in: scale-in var(--animate-duration-fast) var(--ease-spring);
   307→
   308→  @keyframes fade-in {
   309→    from { opacity: 0; }
   310→    to { opacity: 1; }
   311→  }
   312→
   313→  @keyframes slide-up {
   314→    from {
   315→      opacity: 0;
   316→      transform: translateY(1rem);
   317→    }
   318→    to {
   319→      opacity: 1;
   320→      transform: translateY(0);
   321→    }
   322→  }
   323→
   324→  @keyframes scale-in {
   325→    from {
   326→      opacity: 0;
   327→      transform: scale(0.95);
   328→    }
   329→    to {
   330→      opacity: 1;
   331→      transform: scale(1);
   332→    }
   333→  }
   334→}
   335→```
   336→
   337→**Usage:**
   338→```html
   339→<div class="animate-fade-in">Fades in on load</div>
   340→<div class="animate-slide-up hover:animate-scale-in">Interactive</div>
   341→```
   342→
   343→#### Vue 3 Transition Integration
   344→
   345→**Sources:**
   346→- https://vueschool.io/lessons/custom-vue-transition-classes-aka-tailwind-css-with-vue-transitions
   347→- https://stackoverflow.com/questions/68998731/vue-transition-with-tailwind
   348→
   349→**Pattern: Custom Transition Classes:**
   350→```vue
   351→<template>
   352→  <Transition
   353→    enter-active-class="transition duration-300 ease-out"
   354→    enter-from-class="opacity-0 scale-95"
   355→    enter-to-class="opacity-100 scale-100"
   356→    leave-active-class="transition duration-200 ease-in"
   357→    leave-from-class="opacity-100 scale-100"
   358→    leave-to-class="opacity-0 scale-95"
   359→  >
   360→    <div v-if="show" class="modal">Content</div>
   361→  </Transition>
   362→</template>
   363→```
   364→
   365→**Reusable Composable Pattern:**
   366→```typescript
   367→// composables/useTransitionClasses.ts
   368→export const useTransitionClasses = () => ({
   369→  fadeIn: {
   370→    enterActiveClass: 'transition-opacity duration-300',
   371→    enterFromClass: 'opacity-0',
   372→    enterToClass: 'opacity-100',
   373→    leaveActiveClass: 'transition-opacity duration-200',
   374→    leaveFromClass: 'opacity-100',
   375→    leaveToClass: 'opacity-0',
   376→  },
   377→  slideUp: {
   378→    enterActiveClass: 'transition-all duration-300 ease-out',
   379→    enterFromClass: 'opacity-0 translate-y-4',
   380→    enterToClass: 'opacity-100 translate-y-0',
   381→    leaveActiveClass: 'transition-all duration-200 ease-in',
   382→    leaveFromClass: 'opacity-100 translate-y-0',
   383→    leaveToClass: 'opacity-0 translate-y-4',
   384→  },
   385→});
   386→```
   387→
   388→```vue
   389→<script setup lang="ts">
   390→import { useTransitionClasses } from '@/composables/useTransitionClasses';
   391→
   392→const transitions = useTransitionClasses();
   393→</script>
   394→
   395→<template>
   396→  <Transition v-bind="transitions.fadeIn">
   397→    <div v-if="show">Content</div>
   398→  </Transition>
   399→</template>
   400→```
   401→
   402→#### Responsive Animation Scaling
   403→
   404→**Pattern: CSS Variables + Tailwind Responsive Utilities:**
   405→```css
   406→@theme {
   407→  --animate-duration: 300ms;
   408→}
   409→
   410→@layer base {
   411→  /* Reduce motion on mobile */
   412→  @media (max-width: 640px) {
   413→    :root {
   414→      --animate-duration: 200ms;
   415→    }
   416→  }
   417→
   418→  /* Respect user preferences */
   419→  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
   420→    :root {
   421→      --animate-duration: 0ms;
   422→    }
   423→  }
   424→}
   425→```
   426→
   427→**Vue Composable for Responsive Animations:**
   428→```typescript
   429→// composables/useResponsiveAnimation.ts
   430→import { ref, computed, onMounted } from 'vue';
   431→
   432→export const useResponsiveAnimation = () => {
   433→  const prefersReducedMotion = ref(false);
   434→
   435→  onMounted(() => {
   436→    const mediaQuery = window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)');
   437→    prefersReducedMotion.value = mediaQuery.matches;
   438→
   439→    mediaQuery.addEventListener('change', (e) => {
   440→      prefersReducedMotion.value = e.matches;
   441→    });
   442→  });
   443→
   444→  const animationDuration = computed(() => {
   445→    if (prefersReducedMotion.value) return 0;
   446→    return getComputedStyle(document.documentElement)
   447→      .getPropertyValue('--animate-duration');
   448→  });
   449→
   450→  return { animationDuration, prefersReducedMotion };
   451→};
   452→```
   453→
   454→#### Performance Considerations: Web Animations API
   455→
   456→**When to Use:**
   457→- Complex, multi-property animations
   458→- Animations requiring fine-grained control
   459→- Performance-critical animations (runs on compositor thread)
   460→
   461→**Pattern:**
   462→```typescript
   463→// composables/useWebAnimation.ts
   464→export const useWebAnimation = (
   465→  element: Ref<HTMLElement | null>,
   466→  keyframes: Keyframe[],
   467→  options: KeyframeAnimationOptions
   468→) => {
   469→  const animation = ref<Animation | null>(null);
   470→
   471→  const play = () => {
   472→    if (!element.value) return;
   473→
   474→    animation.value = element.value.animate(keyframes, {
   475→      duration: parseInt(
   476→        getComputedStyle(document.documentElement)
   477→          .getPropertyValue('--animate-duration')
   478→      ),
   479→      easing: getComputedStyle(document.documentElement)
   480→        .getPropertyValue('--ease-in-out'),
   481→      ...options,
   482→    });
   483→  };
   484→
   485→  return { play, animation };
   486→};
   487→```
   488→
   489→---
   490→
   491→## 4. Astro + Vue + Tailwind Integration
   492→
   493→### SSR-Safe Tailwind Patterns
   494→
   495→**Sources:**
   496→- https://docs.astro.build/en/guides/styling/
   497→- https://themefisher.com/tailwind-css-with-astro
   498→
   499→#### Setup Configuration
   500→
   501→**Install Tailwind:**
   502→```bash
   503→npx astro add tailwind
   504→```
   505→
   506→**Tailwind Config (`tailwind.config.mjs`):**
   507→```javascript
   508→/** @type {import('tailwindcss').Config} */
   509→export default {
   510→  content: [
   511→    './src/**/*.{astro,html,js,jsx,md,mdx,svelte,ts,tsx,vue}'
   512→  ],
   513→  darkMode: 'class', // Critical for SSR compatibility
   514→  theme: {
   515→    extend: {}, // Use CSS @theme instead in v4
   516→  },
   517→  plugins: [],
   518→}
   519→```
   520→
   521→**Global Styles (`src/styles/global.css`):**
   522→```css
   523→@import "tailwindcss";
   524→
   525→@theme {
   526→  /* Custom design tokens */
   527→  --color-brand: #3f3cbb;
   528→  --font-display: Poppins, sans-serif;
   529→}
   530→
   531→@layer base {
   532→  /* Base styles that affect all pages */
   533→  html {
   534→    font-family: var(--font-display);
   535→  }
   536→}
   537→```
   538→
   539→**Layout Component (`src/layouts/Layout.astro`):**
   540→```astro
   541→---
   542→import '../styles/global.css';
   543→
   544→interface Props {
   545→  title: string;
   546→}
   547→
   548→const { title } = Astro.props;
   549→---
   550→
   551→<!doctype html>
   552→<html lang="en">
   553→  <head>
   554→    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
   555→    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
   556→    <title>{title}</title>
   557→  </head>
   558→  <body class="bg-background text-foreground">
   559→    <slot />
   560→  </body>
   561→</html>
   562→```
   563→
   564→#### Dark Mode Implementation (SSR-Safe)
   565→
   566→**Source:** https://namoku.dev/blog/darkmode-tailwind-astro/
   567→
   568→**Critical Pattern: Inline Script for Flash Prevention**
   569→
   570→```astro
   571→---
   572→// src/layouts/Layout.astro
   573→import '../styles/global.css';
   574→---
   575→
   576→<!doctype html>
   577→<html lang="en">
   578→  <head>
   579→    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
   580→    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
   581→    <title>{title}</title>
   582→
   583→    <!-- CRITICAL: Inline script runs before page render -->
   584→    <script is:inline>
   585→      // IIFE to prevent global scope pollution
   586→      (function() {
   587→        const getTheme = () => {
   588→          // Check localStorage first
   589→          if (typeof localStorage !== 'undefined') {
   590→            const stored = localStorage.getItem('theme');
   591→            if (stored) return stored;
   592→          }
   593→
   594→          // Fall back to system preference
   595→          return window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches
   596→            ? 'dark'
   597→            : 'light';
   598→        };
   599→
   600→        const theme = getTheme();
   601→
   602→        // Apply dark class immediately (before render)
   603→        if (theme === 'dark') {
   604→          document.documentElement.classList.add('dark');
   605→        }
   606→      })();
   607→    </script>
   608→  </head>
   609→  <body>
   610→    <slot />
   611→  </body>
   612→</html>
   613→```
   614→
   615→**⚠️ Key Point:** The `is:inline` directive prevents Astro from bundling/optimizing the script, ensuring it runs synchronously before page render.
   616→
   617→#### View Transitions Dark Mode Persistence
   618→
   619→**Problem:** Astro View Transitions API replaces DOM content, removing the `dark` class.
   620→
   621→**Solution:**
   622→```astro
   623→<script>
   624→  // Theme toggle logic
   625→  function applyTheme() {
   626→    const theme = localStorage.getItem('theme') || 'light';
   627→    document.documentElement.classList.toggle('dark', theme === 'dark');
   628→  }
   629→
   630→  function toggleTheme() {
   631→    const currentTheme = localStorage.getItem('theme') || 'light';
   632→    const newTheme = currentTheme === 'dark' ? 'light' : 'dark';
   633→    localStorage.setItem('theme', newTheme);
   634→    applyTheme();
   635→  }
   636→
   637→  // Apply on initial load
   638→  applyTheme();
   639→
   640→  // Reapply after View Transitions navigation
   641→  document.addEventListener('astro:after-swap', () => {
   642→    applyTheme();
   643→
   644→    // Reattach event listeners (removed during swap)
   645→    const themeToggle = document.getElementById('themeToggle');
   646→    if (themeToggle && !themeToggle.hasAttribute('onclick')) {
   647→      themeToggle.addEventListener('click', toggleTheme);
   648→    }
   649→  });
   650→</script>
   651→
   652→<button id="themeToggle" type="button">
   653→  Toggle Theme
   654→</button>
   655→```
   656→
   657→**Event Lifecycle:**
   658→- `astro:before-preparation` - Before new page fetch
   659→- `astro:after-preparation` - After new page fetch
   660→- `astro:before-swap` - Before DOM replacement
   661→- **`astro:after-swap`** - **Use this for theme persistence**
   662→- `astro:page-load` - After navigation complete
   663→
   664→#### Vue Component Tailwind Class Hydration
   665→
   666→**SSR-Safe Pattern:**
   667→```vue
   668→<script setup lang="ts">
   669→import { ref, onMounted } from 'vue';
   670→
   671→// Safe: Static classes (hydrated correctly)
   672→const baseClasses = 'bg-primary text-white px-4 py-2 rounded';
   673→
   674→// Dangerous: Dynamic classes computed during SSR
   675→// const dynamicClasses = computed(() => {
   676→//   return isDark.value ? 'bg-gray-900' : 'bg-white'; // ❌ SSR mismatch
   677→// });
   678→
   679→// Safe: Dynamic classes after mount
   680→const themeClasses = ref('');
   681→
   682→onMounted(() => {
   683→  const theme = localStorage.getItem('theme');
   684→  themeClasses.value = theme === 'dark' ? 'bg-gray-900' : 'bg-white';
   685→});
   686→</script>
   687→
   688→<template>
   689→  <button :class="[baseClasses, themeClasses]">
   690→    Click me
   691→  </button>
   692→</template>
   693→```
   694→
   695→**Alternative: CSS Variable Strategy (Preferred):**
   696→```vue
   697→<script setup lang="ts">
   698→// No JavaScript needed - CSS handles theme reactivity
   699→</script>
   700→
   701→<template>
   702→  <button class="bg-background text-foreground hover:bg-primary">
   703→    Click me
   704→  </button>
   705→</template>
   706→
   707→<style scoped>
   708→/* Tailwind utilities automatically respond to .dark class */
   709→</style>
   710→```
   711→
   712→#### Global Styles Organization
   713→
   714→**Recommended Directory Structure:**
   715→```
   716→src/
   717→├── styles/
   718→│   ├── global.css         # Tailwind imports + @theme
   719→│   ├── base.css           # Base element styles
   720→│   ├── components.css     # Component-layer styles
   721→│   └── utilities.css      # Custom utility classes
   722→├── layouts/
   723→│   └── Layout.astro       # Imports global.css
   724→└── components/
   725→    └── (Vue components)
   726→```
   727→
   728→**global.css Pattern:**
   729→```css
   730→/* src/styles/global.css */
   731→@import "tailwindcss";
   732→
   733→/* Design tokens */
   734→@theme {
   735→  --color-brand: #3f3cbb;
   736→  --font-display: Poppins, sans-serif;
   737→  --spacing-section: 6rem;
   738→}
   739→
   740→/* Base styles */
   741→@layer base {
   742→  html {
   743→    @apply scroll-smooth;
   744→  }
   745→
   746→  body {
   747→    @apply font-sans antialiased;
   748→  }
   749→
   750→  h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6 {
   751→    @apply font-display font-bold;
   752→  }
   753→}
   754→
   755→/* Component patterns (reusable) */
   756→@layer components {
   757→  .btn {
   758→    @apply px-4 py-2 rounded font-medium transition-colors;
   759→  }
   760→
   761→  .btn-primary {
   762→    @apply btn bg-primary text-white hover:bg-primary-hover;
   763→  }
   764→}
   765→
   766→/* Custom utilities */
   767→@layer utilities {
   768→  .text-balance {
   769→    text-wrap: balance;
   770→  }
   771→}
   772→```
   773→
   774→**Import Strategy:**
   775→```astro
   776→---
   777→// src/layouts/Layout.astro
   778→// Import once in layout, available globally
   779→import '../styles/global.css';
   780→---
   781→```
   782→
   783→**❌ Anti-Pattern:**
   784→```vue
   785→<!-- Don't import global.css in Vue components -->
   786→<script setup lang="ts">
   787→import '@/styles/global.css'; // ❌ Duplicates styles
   788→</script>
   789→```
   790→
   791→---
   792→
   793→## 5. Plugin Architecture
   794→
   795→### When to Create Plugins vs Utilities
   796→
   797→**Source:** https://tailwindcss.com/docs/plugins
   798→
   799→#### Decision Framework
   800→
   801→| Use Case | Solution | Reasoning |
   802→|----------|----------|-----------|
   803→| Single CSS property | `@utility` directive | Simpler, less overhead |
   804→| Multi-property pattern | `@utility` with nesting | Keeps CSS together |
   805→| Complex component base styles | Plugin with `addComponents` | Semantic, reusable |
   806→| New variants (custom selectors) | `@custom-variant` directive | Built-in support in v4 |
   807→| JavaScript-generated utilities | Plugin with `matchUtilities` | Dynamic value generation |
   808→
   809→#### Custom Utilities (Preferred for Most Cases)
   810→
   811→**Simple Utility:**
   812→```css
   813→@utility content-auto {
   814→  content-visibility: auto;
   815→}
   816→
   817→/* Generates: */
   818→.content-auto { content-visibility: auto; }
   819→```
   820→
   821→**Multi-Property Utility:**
   822→```css
   823→@utility scrollbar-hidden {
   824→  &::-webkit-scrollbar {
   825→    display: none;
   826→  }
   827→
   828→  scrollbar-width: none;
   829→}
   830→
   831→/* Generates with variants: */
   832→.scrollbar-hidden::-webkit-scrollbar { display: none; }
   833→.hover\:scrollbar-hidden:hover::-webkit-scrollbar { display: none; }
   834→```
   835→
   836→**Parameterized Utility:**
   837→```css
   838→@utility tab-* {
   839→  tab-size: --value(--tab-size-*);
   840→}
   841→
   842→/* Usage: tab-4, tab-8, tab-[12] */
   843→```
   844→
   845→**Value Function Capabilities:**
   846→```css
   847→@utility leading-* {
   848→  /* Theme matching */
   849→  line-height: --value(--line-height-*);
   850→
   851→  /* Bare values */
   852→  /* --value(integer) - unitless numbers */
   853→  /* --value(percentage) - percentage values */
   854→
   855→  /* Literal values */
   856→  /* --value("inherit", "initial") */
   857→
   858→  /* Arbitrary values */
   859→  /* --value([length], [percentage]) */
   860→}
   861→```
   862→
   863→#### Custom Variants (v4 Pattern)
   864→
   865→**Role-Based Variant:**
   866→```css
   867→@custom-variant theme-midnight {
   868→  &:where([data-theme="midnight"] *) {
   869→    @slot;
   870→  }
   871→}
   872→
   873→/* Usage: theme-midnight:bg-purple-900 */
   874→```
   875→
   876→**State Variant:**
   877→```css
   878→@custom-variant group-loading {
   879→  :merge(.group)[data-loading] & {
   880→    @slot;
   881→  }
   882→}
   883→
   884→/* Usage: group-loading:opacity-50 */
   885→```
   886→
   887→**Media Query Variant:**
   888→```css
   889→@custom-variant motion-safe {
   890→  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) {
   891→    @slot;
   892→  }
   893→}
   894→
   895→/* Usage: motion-safe:animate-fade-in */
   896→```
   897→
   898→#### Plugin Patterns (v3 and Legacy Support)
   899→
   900→**When to Use Plugins:**
   901→- Supporting Tailwind v3 projects
   902→- Complex JavaScript logic for utility generation
   903→- Third-party libraries/design systems
   904→- Advanced theme manipulation
   905→
   906→**Component Plugin Pattern:**
   907→```javascript
   908→// plugins/components.js
   909→const plugin = require('tailwindcss/plugin');
   910→
   911→module.exports = plugin(function({ addComponents, theme }) {
   912→  addComponents({
   913→    '.card': {
   914→      backgroundColor: theme('colors.white'),
   915→      borderRadius: theme('borderRadius.lg'),
   916→      padding: theme('spacing.6'),
   917→      boxShadow: theme('boxShadow.xl'),
   918→    },
   919→    '.card-dark': {
   920→      backgroundColor: theme('colors.gray.800'),
   921→      color: theme('colors.white'),
   922→    },
   923→  });
   924→});
   925→```
   926→
   927→**Dynamic Utility Plugin:**
   928→```javascript
   929→// plugins/utilities.js
   930→const plugin = require('tailwindcss/plugin');
   931→
   932→module.exports = plugin(function({ matchUtilities, theme }) {
   933→  matchUtilities(
   934→    {
   935→      'grid-cols-fit': (value) => ({
   936→        gridTemplateColumns: `repeat(auto-fit, minmax(${value}, 1fr))`,
   937→      }),
   938→    },
   939→    { values: theme('spacing') }
   940→  );
   941→});
   942→
   943→// Usage: grid-cols-fit-64, grid-cols-fit-[200px]
   944→```
   945→
   946→**Variant Plugin:**
   947→```javascript
   948→// plugins/variants.js
   949→const plugin = require('tailwindcss/plugin');
   950→
   951→module.exports = plugin(function({ addVariant }) {
   952→  addVariant('third', '&:nth-child(3)');
   953→  addVariant('hocus', ['&:hover', '&:focus']);
   954→
   955→  // Complex selector
   956→  addVariant('supports-grid', '@supports (display: grid)');
   957→});
   958→
   959→// Usage: third:font-bold, hocus:underline
   960→```
   961→
   962→#### Plugin File Organization
   963→
   964→**Monolithic (Small Projects):**
   965→```javascript
   966→// tailwind.config.js
   967→module.exports = {
   968→  plugins: [
   969→    require('@tailwindcss/forms'),
   970→    require('./plugins/custom'),
   971→  ],
   972→};
   973→```
   974→
   975→**Modular (Design Systems/Large Projects):**
   976→```
   977→plugins/
   978→├── index.js              # Aggregates all plugins
   979→├── components/
   980→│   ├── buttons.js
   981→│   ├── cards.js
   982→│   └── forms.js
   983→├── utilities/
   984→│   ├── grid.js
   985→│   ├── typography.js
   986→│   └── spacing.js
   987→└── variants/
   988→    ├── states.js
   989→    └── themes.js
   990→```
   991→
   992→```javascript
   993→// plugins/index.js
   994→const components = require('./components');
   995→const utilities = require('./utilities');
   996→const variants = require('./variants');
   997→
   998→module.exports = [
   999→  components,
  1000→  utilities,
  1001→  variants,
  1002→];
  1003→
  1004→// tailwind.config.js
  1005→module.exports = {
  1006→  plugins: require('./plugins'),
  1007→};
  1008→```
  1009→
  1010→---
  1011→
  1012→## 6. Design System Examples & Industry Patterns
  1013→
  1014→### Shadcn/UI Approach (CSS Variables + Semantic Naming)
  1015→
  1016→**Pattern:** Define all colors as CSS variables, use semantic utility classes
  1017→
  1018→```css
  1019→@layer base {
  1020→  :root {
  1021→    --background: 0 0% 100%;
  1022→    --foreground: 222.2 84% 4.9%;
  1023→    --card: 0 0% 100%;
  1024→    --card-foreground: 222.2 84% 4.9%;
  1025→    --primary: 222.2 47.4% 11.2%;
  1026→    --primary-foreground: 210 40% 98%;
  1027→    --destructive: 0 84.2% 60.2%;
  1028→    --destructive-foreground: 210 40% 98%;
  1029→    --radius: 0.5rem;
  1030→  }
  1031→
  1032→  .dark {
  1033→    --background: 222.2 84% 4.9%;
  1034→    --foreground: 210 40% 98%;
  1035→    --card: 222.2 84% 4.9%;
  1036→    --card-foreground: 210 40% 98%;
  1037→    --primary: 210 40% 98%;
  1038→    --primary-foreground: 222.2 47.4% 11.2%;
  1039→    --destructive: 0 62.8% 30.6%;
  1040→    --destructive-foreground: 210 40% 98%;
  1041→  }
  1042→}
  1043→
  1044→@layer base {
  1045→  * {
  1046→    @apply border-border;
  1047→  }
  1048→  body {
  1049→    @apply bg-background text-foreground;
  1050→  }
  1051→}
  1052→```
  1053→
  1054→**Benefits:**
  1055→- Theme switching via CSS variable override
  1056→- HSL format allows opacity modifiers: `bg-primary/50`
  1057→- Semantic names survive redesigns
  1058→
  1059→### Radix UI/Headless UI Pattern (Unstyled Components + Tailwind)
  1060→
  1061→**Pattern:** Headless components with Tailwind styling via props
  1062→
  1063→```vue
  1064→<script setup lang="ts">
  1065→import { Dialog, DialogPanel, DialogTitle } from '@headlessui/vue';
  1066→
  1067→const isOpen = ref(false);
  1068→</script>
  1069→
  1070→<template>
  1071→  <Dialog
  1072→    :open="isOpen"
  1073→    @close="isOpen = false"
  1074→    class="relative z-50"
  1075→  >
  1076→    <!-- Backdrop -->
  1077→    <div class="fixed inset-0 bg-black/30" aria-hidden="true" />
  1078→
  1079→    <!-- Panel -->
  1080→    <div class="fixed inset-0 flex items-center justify-center p-4">
  1081→      <DialogPanel class="mx-auto max-w-sm rounded bg-white p-6 shadow-xl">
  1082→        <DialogTitle class="text-lg font-medium">
  1083→          Deactivate account
  1084→        </DialogTitle>
  1085→        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500">
  1086→          Are you sure you want to deactivate your account?
  1087→        </p>
  1088→        <div class="mt-4 flex gap-2">
  1089→          <button
  1090→            class="btn-primary"
  1091→            @click="isOpen = false"
  1092→          >
  1093→            Deactivate
  1094→          </button>
  1095→          <button
  1096→            class="btn-secondary"
  1097→            @click="isOpen = false"
  1098→          >
  1099→            Cancel
  1100→          </button>
  1101→        </div>
  1102→      </DialogPanel>
  1103→    </div>
  1104→  </Dialog>
  1105→</template>
  1106→```
  1107→
  1108→**Benefits:**
  1109→- Accessibility built-in (focus management, ARIA)
  1110→- Full styling control via Tailwind
  1111→- No CSS conflicts or specificity issues
  1112→
  1113→---
  1114→
  1115→## 7. Key Takeaways & Action Items
  1116→
  1117→### Immediate Implementation Steps
  1118→
  1119→1. **Migrate to Tailwind v4 CSS Configuration**
  1120→   - Replace `tailwind.config.js` theme with `@theme` directive
  1121→   - Define semantic color tokens with dark mode variants
  1122→   - Use `@utility` for custom utilities instead of plugins
  1123→
  1124→2. **Implement SSR-Safe Dark Mode**
  1125→   - Use `is:inline` script in Astro layout for flash prevention
  1126→   - Add `astro:after-swap` listener for View Transitions persistence
  1127→   - Store theme preference in localStorage with system fallback
  1128→
  1129→3. **Centralize Animation System**
  1130→   - Define animation tokens via `@theme` (durations, easings, keyframes)
  1131→   - Create Vue composables for Transition class sets
  1132→   - Implement `prefers-reduced-motion` checks
  1133→
  1134→4. **Organize Global Styles**
  1135→   - Single import in layout component (`src/styles/global.css`)
  1136→   - Use `@layer base` for element defaults
  1137→   - Use `@layer components` for reusable patterns
  1138→   - Use `@layer utilities` for custom utility classes
  1139→
  1140→5. **Adopt Semantic Color Naming**
  1141→   - Replace literal names (`blue-500`) with role-based (`primary`, `foreground`)
  1142→   - Define dark mode as CSS variable overrides
  1143→   - Use HSL format for opacity modifier support
  1144→
  1145→### Anti-Patterns to Avoid
  1146→
  1147→❌ **Don't:** Compute Tailwind classes dynamically during SSR
  1148→```vue
  1149→<!-- Bad: SSR hydration mismatch -->
  1150→<div :class="isDark ? 'bg-gray-900' : 'bg-white'">
  1151→```
  1152→
  1153→✅ **Do:** Use CSS variables for theme reactivity
  1154→```vue
  1155→<!-- Good: CSS handles reactivity -->
  1156→<div class="bg-background">
  1157→```
  1158→
  1159→---
  1160→
  1161→❌ **Don't:** Import global styles in Vue components
  1162→```vue
  1163→<script setup lang="ts">
  1164→import '@/styles/global.css'; // ❌ Duplicates
  1165→</script>
  1166→```
  1167→
  1168→✅ **Do:** Import once in Astro layout
  1169→```astro
  1170→---
  1171→import '../styles/global.css'; // ✅ Single import
  1172→---
  1173→```
  1174→
  1175→---
  1176→
  1177→❌ **Don't:** Create plugins for simple utilities
  1178→```javascript
  1179→// Over-engineered
  1180→plugin(({ addUtilities }) => {
  1181→  addUtilities({ '.content-auto': { 'content-visibility': 'auto' } });
  1182→});
  1183→```
  1184→
  1185→✅ **Do:** Use `@utility` directive
  1186→```css
  1187→@utility content-auto {
  1188→  content-visibility: auto;
  1189→}
  1190→```
  1191→
  1192→---
  1193→
  1194→❌ **Don't:** Use `theme` to override (removes defaults)
  1195→```javascript
  1196→module.exports = {
  1197→  theme: {
  1198→    colors: { primary: '#3f3cbb' } // ❌ Removes all default colors
  1199→  }
  1200→}
  1201→```
  1202→
  1203→✅ **Do:** Use `@theme` to extend
  1204→```css
  1205→@theme {
  1206→  --color-primary: #3f3cbb; /* ✅ Adds to defaults */
  1207→}
  1208→```
  1209→
  1210→### Performance Optimizations
  1211→
  1212→1. **Purge Unused Styles**
  1213→   - Ensure `content` array includes all template files
  1214→   - Use PurgeCSS safelist for dynamic classes
  1215→
  1216→2. **Minimize CSS Variable Lookups**
  1217→   - Use `@theme inline` when referencing other variables
  1218→   - Avoid deeply nested variable references
  1219→
  1220→3. **Optimize Animations**
  1221→   - Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`
  1222→   - Use `will-change` sparingly (only during animation)
  1223→   - Prefer `transform` and `opacity` for GPU acceleration
  1224→
  1225→4. **Code Splitting**
  1226→   - Import component-specific styles via dynamic imports
  1227→   - Use Astro's built-in CSS bundling for critical styles
  1228→
  1229→---
  1230→
  1231→## Sources Referenced
  1232→
  1233→1. **Tailwind CSS v4 Theme Documentation**
  1234→   https://tailwindcss.com/docs/theme
  1235→   *Theme variables, @theme directive, namespace organization*
  1236→
  1237→2. **Simon Swiss - Tailwind v4 Multi-Theme Strategy**
  1238→   https://simonswiss.com/posts/tailwind-v4-multi-theme
  1239→   *CSS variable patterns, semantic color naming, dark mode*
  1240→
  1241→3. **Namoku.dev - Dark Mode with Tailwind and Astro**
  1242→   https://namoku.dev/blog/darkmode-tailwind-astro/
  1243→   *SSR-safe implementation, View Transitions persistence*
  1244→
  1245→4. **Tailwind CSS Plugins Documentation**
  1246→   https://tailwindcss.com/docs/plugins
  1247→   *Plugin architecture, addUtilities, matchUtilities patterns*
  1248→
  1249→5. **Astro Styling Documentation**
  1250→   https://docs.astro.build/en/guides/styling/
  1251→   *Global styles organization, CSS import strategies*
  1252→
  1253→6. **Vue School - Custom Transition Classes**
  1254→   https://vueschool.io/lessons/custom-vue-transition-classes-aka-tailwind-css-with-vue-transitions
  1255→   *Vue 3 Transition integration with Tailwind utilities*
  1256→
  1257→7. **Motion.dev - Tailwind Integration Guide**
  1258→   https://motion.dev/docs/react-tailwind
  1259→   *Animation architecture, responsive animation scaling*
  1260→
  1261→8. **Stack Overflow - Tailwind v4 Theme Variables**
  1262→   https://stackoverflow.com/questions/79691837/how-to-override-theme-variables-in-tailwindcss-v4-theme-vs-layer-theme-vs-r
  1263→   *@theme vs @layer theme vs :root clarification*
  1264→
  1265→9. **Theme Fisher - Integrating Tailwind with Astro**
  1266→   https://themefisher.com/tailwind-css-with-astro
  1267→   *Setup guide, configuration patterns*
